 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maladominus>Maladominus</A> at: 12/3/02 1:55:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dididaryth>Didi D Aryth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Worshipping Tallonar since 3160</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/02 4:49:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=344.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/didi/a_didisig.gif height=120 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinkerfest Planning Thread</span><hr size=1> Well!  Better be gettin' down to business, barely over a week to go!  <br>
<br>
I see a bunch of great ideas on the Saga boards so here is a verbatim quote:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Friday = starting day of Tinkerfest 3-day festival, and all gnomes in Norrath are encouraged to kick off the holiday by greeting fellow gnomes (or non-gnomes?) with the greeting Happy Tinkerfest! <br>
<br>
Even if a gnome has no idea about Tinkerfest, greet them anyways. Even if a gnome player does not RP, greet them anyways. <br>
<br>
The most likely outcome will be a look in their face like &quot;Huh?? What are you talking about? What the hell is Tinkerfest? This sounds like a fun event of some kind? Am I missing out on some kind of secret here? Can you please tell me more?&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
On Friday, I will see about setting up minor events in Akanon to start off the holiday. As an idea, I might hold random raffles.... as an incentive for players just being back home in Akanon during the 'holidays'. This is one day where we can brainstorm more events if desired. <br>
<br>
<br>
Saturday = 2nd Day, the big day for Tinkerfest. This is the day where we throw all the punches, all the fireworks are let loose, rowdy celebration, and hopefully as many gnomes and guests we can pack in Steamfont and Akanon for most of the day. Events should be ongoing for most of the day. <br>
<br>
If there is a day when our GMs and Guides can attend to help out, this would be the day I would like to see them show up. This would also be the day we would hold some of the larger events, especially those that give out the largest incentives (awards, prizes) for attendance. <br>
<br>
Someone also suggested a choreographed fireworks display when it gets dark outside in Steamfont. <br>
<br>
Most likely the biggest events may take place sometime around mid-afternoon or early evening time (Pacific Time). But for those people on CET or EST or other time zones, dont worry, because I would like to see the events still sporadically spread out for most of the day. <br>
<br>
Think of it like one giant open-house party where guests come and go, but the flow of beer never stops, and the party lights itself never go out all day long. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Sunday = last day of Tinkerfest, winding down the holiday. This is still considered part of the holiday, even if not as rowdy and cheery as the Tinkerfest Saturday. I would still greet other gnomes with a Happy Tinkerfest. And time and volunteers allowing, we can still hold some minor events for some part of Sunday..... especially for those players who missed out (or could not attend) events from the previous two days. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Now here are my specific thoughts:<br>
<br>
Friday: everybody everywhere wish everybody happy Tinkerfest and hand out alcohol - preferably gnomish spirits, I would think!<br>
<br>
Friday event in Steamfont - 10pm EST / 7pm PST - drunken opening celebrations.  Possibly involving:<br>
<br>
- story telling in the throne room of King Ak'Anon: Mal can recite the history of Tinkerfest (hehe happy hotkeying) in /shout.  Someone outside to shout regular announcements and direct people inside.<br>
<br>
- appointment of Prince and Princess Ak'Anon for the holiday.  I suggest all interested contestants are paired up in dice rolls, e.g. if 8 women interested, 4 pairs roll off, then the 4 winners roll in 2 pairs, then the 2 winners roll off.  (Odd numbers can roll against a judge, if the judge wins, nobody procedes to next round.)  Winners are then awarded something or other, announced in Ak'Anon, Steamfont, the Bazaar, and possibly the market channel.<br>
<br>
- following the story and crowning, drunken race to the PoD.  Gnomes must consume 1 stack of gnomish spirits, and run from King to PoD without falling in the water.  Any who do, receive a prize (platinum, a geerlok device, something like that.)  The newly appointed Prince and Princess can start the races off and/or announce the winners (maybe Prince starts, Princess names winners for example).<br>
<br>
- clockwork pinatas (Sabbik's idea): is it still possible to give items to monsters?  If so, I suggest 'spiking' all the clockworks in Steamfont with some low level but decent item - tinkered fireworks, purity belts, recondite bandit armour, maybe a couple of platinum coins. Party can then drunkenly spill outside for drunken clockwork slaying and general festivity.  Those who wish to continue drinking, I suggest an all-out assault on the minotaur slavers to clear and set up base camp at the pavilion,  free the slaves, which gives an excellent excuse for further drinking.  Pinatas and drinking can continue as long as there is alcohol, and someone walking straight enough to continue spiking the clockworks.<br>
<br>
Saturday:  main day.  Starting 1pm PST (9pm London, which means Euro players can join) and continuing for 4 hours (probably as long as we can stand).  We'll have to find out how exactly the GMs can participate - can they make non-gnome celebrants into gnome form, for example?  Whatever they can do, their help would be great.  Players can continue the clockwork pinatas, and we could set up one or more player quests.  For this we would need some volunteers to essentially be a player NPC, with scripted hotkeys acting just like a quest NPC.  We can send players around to recite bits of the Tinkerquest legend to other NPC-players, and receive something (e.g. a tinkered firework, some gnomish spirits, etc.) in return.  They could also collect a number of items and hand them in for a larger award, like a minor geerlok device - hopefully up and coming tinkers would be willing to donate their extras.  Whoever accepts the final turn-ins would have to be near a bank, or we'd have to have some runners assigned to keep refilling their supplies.  Whatever they turn in would need to stack, too!  =)  Maybe clockwork bits, spiderling silks, things like that.  Or alcohol from Luclin - which they can all get to fairly easily via the G Fay spire even if they don't have PoP - the alcohol could then be recycled for minor quest rewards or clockwork pinatas.<br>
<br>
- in the evening, after we're all sick of running the questing: gather all the gnomes we can find and invade key areas en masse shouting Tinkerfest carols.  Areas like the Nexus and Bazaar, but also more unexpected areas like Velketors (for higher level gnomes - could just zone in quickly), Paw, Paludal Caverns, Queynos (for PoP enabled gnomes), Dawnshroud Peaks.  More populated zones where you wouldn't expect mass gnomishness.<br>
<br>
Sunday (and possibly Saturday evening): quiet Tinkerfest gift exchange.  Small &lt;5pp gifts and tokens between friends, or perhaps just gifts of food/alcohol.  Wish everybody you meet a happy Tinkerfest.<br>
<br>
<br>
Whew... that's my thoughts.<br>
<br>
We need to set up a private area for scripting the player quests, the announcements, and the carols.  And to assign responsibilities and duties.  There'll need to be a tinkerfest coordination channel for those helping organize, so that any quest person can shout for help if they run out of quest supplies, or need to go AFK someone can go stand with them and take over if necessary, stuff like that.  Time's a running short and there's lots of planning to be done!<br>
